In article &lt;3553@sater.cs.vu.nl&gt; sater@cs.vu.nl (Hans van Staveren) writes:

   I wonder if some of you out there could check what you can find of
   cs.vu.nl from your part of the domain tree, for example try finding the
   address of the machine top.cs.vu.nl, and how your mailer reacts to my
   address sater@cs.vu.nl.  If you cannot reach me under that name I would

Your network 192.31.231 doesn't seem to have connected status.  Mail
will work from Internet to top.cs.vu.nl, since there is an MX to
hp4nl.nluug.nl and it is on a connected network.  Things get worse
with cs.vu.nl since none of cs.vu.nl's nameservers seem to be on a
connected network.

I have during the past week had trouble with another nl site as well.
Looks like the NS management in NL hsa not stressed enough the fact
that each domain has to have at least one name server on a connected
network or otherwise things break.  On the other hand, why can't you
apply connected status for your network?

-- Juha Heinanen
